2019/03/19

Requires GNU make and git.
Uses the system python (I have python 2.7.10).
May assume MacOS (I have Darwin-MacOS_10.13.6-x86_64).
Assumes that you don't have root.

Edit the user configuration in Makefile.
Run `make prepare` to install odfpy from its git repository.
Run `make run` to invoke a python that can find the installed odfpy.


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2019/03/12

export PYTHONPATH=/Users/andybennett/git/odf-prototype/lib/lib/python2.7/site-packages


INSTALLING ODFPY
----------------

https://github.com/eea/odfpy

git clone https://github.com/eea/odfpy.git
cd odfpy/
python setup.py build
python setup.py install --prefix=/Users/andybennett/git/odf-prototype/lib

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2019/03/27

INSTALLING OPENPYXL
-------------------

export PYTHONPATH=/Users/andybennett/git/odf-prototype/lib/lib/python2.7/site-packages

easy_install --prefix=/Users/andybennett/git/odf-prototype/lib pip
lib/bin/pip install --prefix=/Users/andybennett/git/odf-prototype/lib openpyxl


RUNNING GARETH'S POC
--------------------

export PYTHONPATH=/Users/andybennett/git/odf-prototype/lib/lib/python2.7/site-packages

# Edit the file path in excelImport.py

python excelImport.py

